						               													<description>Aliens: Hadley's Hope is a game set in the Alien universe based on the 1979 science fiction horror film. Players form a cooperative team and try to save colonists from a damaged spaceship and escape, trying not to be killed by the xenomorphs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One player, whose identity is hidden from the rest, has a mission to sabotage the escape. Throughout the entire game no player is eliminated, but if you get killed as a human, you take on the role as the xenomorph they spawned.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the game, players move across a modular board with circular sections that can rotate and change the composition of the maze to their advantage or to block other players. Threats and items come up, and each round xenomorphs move towards human players. If you gather enough items to make it through the sectors alive, find enough colonists and escape safely taking them with you, you win!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
